= WorldArt

The code, issue tracker and wiki can be found at:

* http://github.com/pmisters/WorldArt

== DESCRIPTION:

This packages allows you to access publicly available data from World-art.ru

== FEATURES/PROBLEMS:

WorldArt currently features the following:

* Querying details movie info
* Searching for movies

== SYNOPSIS:

Movies:

  movie = Worldart::Movie.new 24154

  movie.title
  #=> "Ученик чародея"
  movie.cast_members.first
  #=> "Николас Кейдж"

Searching:

  search = Worldart::Search.new "Начало"

  search.movies.size
  #=> 21

== REQUIREMENTS:

All required gems are installed automagically through RubyGems.

* Hpricot 0.8.1

== TESTING:

You'll need rspec and fakeweb installed to run the specs. Y

  $ gem install rspec fakeweb
  $ rake spec

Although not recommended, you may run the specs against the live world-art.ru
website. This will make a lot of calls to world-art.ru, use it wisely.

  $ LIVE_TEST=true rake spec

To update the packaged fixtures files with actual world-art.ru samples, use the
fixtures:refresh rake task

  $ rake fixtures:refresh

